caption: Love this place! Can't wait until we can dine I'm there again.
Great food as always I missed this spot.

i knew from the first taste of the thai iced tea this place was legit. my favorite, delicious drink, you can taste the brewed tea. chicken teriyaki was very flavorful like it was grilled, came with fries and salad. we also got pad thai with wide noodle which was the best pad thai ive had in a minute. we got spring rolls for an appetizer and banana with sticky rice for dessert. overall everything was delicious and we'll be ordering from here more often! also i recommend ordering off their website, you get 10% off the first order
First off, do like this place but my last Experience With ordering, I found a egg shells in not just one not two but all three of the meals i ordered.
The perfect Pad Thai🔥
Best thai food, I've had in chicago

Best Thai Food in Wicker Park!  I love this place. Sometimes, I will order take out from them 3-4 times a week because the food there is so good.  I don't go there as much because I'm trying to save money but I highly recommend this restaurant for people looking for a quick bite that tastes really good.  The Chicken Fried rice and Pad Thai are amazing! Service is excellent
Delicious. We ordered take out and it was still piping hot when we got home. Good size portions and absolutely delish
Without a doubt, the best thai food in town! No frills, fair prices.
This is such a wonderful place.  You cannot go wrong with anything on the menu. Only open for pick up and delivery due to COVID.  They make it very convenient ordering online and over the phone.

There are a number of Thai restaurants in the area; I only order from here. Once my order took a few minutes longer than the estimate and the host have me an iced tea for the wait, so nice! I like to support them by ordering directly, I've found that more accurate.
Best pad thai in the neighborhood!
I ordered chicken and I received Tofu
Mediocre.
Love this place & miss sitting down to eat but greatful that they took such care in packing our delish food to go.
Awesome food
Good food, and very nice employees. I appreciate the COVID measures they're taking (all take out, multiple bill signing stations, hand sanitizer).
Great food with fast, friendly service. We've been getting pickup from there weekly during the pandemic.

I usually get the Pad Thai when I order and it never disappoints! The Pad Thai has the perfect balance and blend of ingredients making it a savory dish. The sauce that they provide on the side is also delicious and compliments the dish well.
The best pad thai — everything here is super fresh. I love love love this neighborhood staple.

On average I probably eat from here once a week. Everything I've had has been so good, always quick and hot. They seem to have a really streamlined setup going while dine-in is prohibited, which is a relief because I would be lost without Thai Lagoon.
Never saw a lagoon
This spot obviously knows how to take care of their customers. Regularly with a very friendly attitude. The food is conveniently priced, regularly delicious and neat.
Would certainly recommend eating here. Excellent ambience, flavorful dishes, great service. Keep it up.
I always order my thai food from Thai Lagoon. I've tried other places, but none compare to this place. I love their chicken egg rolls, chicken gyozas, pad thai and beef fried rice the best.😍😍😍
I never review places but I’m going out of my way to say this is the best Thai restaurant in Chicago. I’ve lived here for 14 years. Must order crab rangoon.
I had a bug in my food. Better try other places this one looks terrible inside doesn't look hygienic.
Good experience and good dinner. Don’t come here looking for vegan magic. That’s all nonsense anyway

Amazing, cosy and affordable Thai place with most delicious food!  I’ve been there recently with my friends, and we all had different dishes, all extremely tasty! You also get a LOT food on your plate for a great price-value! Beautifully decorated, friendly service and cosy environment!  This is my new go-to Thai place in Chicago Wicker Park area!
Affordable and authentic food, BYOB, and a must have on you shortlist of delivery restaurants

I had the Woonsen Pad Thai with tofu and it was delicious! They make their pad thais with tamarind sauce (instead of fish sauce) and I'm a big fan of that as a vegetarian. Great food, great service, and cool decorations/art on the walls!
Great food for carrying out, but indifferent service and ambience out of a film student's final project make this hard to love.
The customer service is regularly rapid, good vibes, super nice staff. I will visit again when I arrive nearby.

I always get the chicken fried rice lunch special (non spicy) and its soooo delicious! Also you get soup of the day and egg rolls with the lunch special too. The service is nice and this place feels really cozy. Me and my co workers always come here for lunch!
Very tasty! Great value.
Best Thai food in the city. Great portions and not crowded (at least when I've been there) on street parking never has been a problem.
Always good!
Great Tom Yum soup, pretty good pad thai. Amazing crispy rice chiken app Nomsad I think. Slow service seemingly do to brisk take out biz. Cold by constantly opening door. Great place to get delivery!

You used to be my favorite restaurant until you stopped carrying fresh (or even frozen) Thai chili peppers. Now I'm so disappointed you just use dried chili flakes to make your food 'spicy'. Fresh is soooooo much better!  If you start to carry fresh chilis again to use in your food I will be your loyal and dedicated customer and place an order multiple times per week. Please consider this and let me know if you make a change. Thank you!

We came to this restaurant for dinner. my friend recommended this spot.  Well, we were not disappointed. we were warmly welcomed by the crew  and we had a fantastic feeling. The food was just great. We enjoyed every moment and we shall absolutely come back again. Highly recommended.
I've been coming here for years, always a great go to for Thai food.
Delicious and fast. The food is way better nice and hot eating in than ordering out!
Amazing food, and the best, and spiciest, Miso soup ever.  They sometimes have issues with take out orders not going though or periodically getting something wrong but they try to make up for it.
The best Thai food I have been
I have had good and no so good service ! Food is good . Great lunch specials!
This place was absolutely disappointing. Nothing fresh. Ordered cashew chicken, got chicken nugget meat with nuts thrown on it . Don’t bother
Always fast,fresh, delicious,and not expensive.

Tried this place out for a change, wouldn’t come back. I can see why everyone gets take out. Firstly, the building reeked of natural gas. The staff were not concerned, just mentioned we could sit somewhere else. Ha! The waiters and hostess were crabby, and cold. Nothing cordial about their customer service (or I should say complete lack of it!).  Tried repeatedly to explain we were vegan, but they couldn’t quite grasp the concept. The food was decent. No quality issues, but i wouldn’t go out of my way to come back for it. Not memorable. The interior art was neat....that’s the only positive I can really give this place
Awesome food, nice place!
Cheap, delicious. Best crab Rangoon I’ve literally ever had
SO GOOD
Amazing atmosphere and great food
(Translated by Google) Very rich! excellent price and very good taste  (Original) Muy rico!  excelente precio y muy buen sabor
Good Thai food!
Love the food, never disappointed with my order.
Food made fresh while you wait. Mushroom wontons and salads are great. Recommend.
Delicious and very affordable! The chicken satay is the best I've had in the city. The service is fast and friendly.
Wonderful food!!!
Best lunch deal in wicker Park! Skip the crowds and go get some curry.

The table was sort of sticky  and could have used a good wipe down with a good cleaning agent to get the buildup off of it.  Pad Thai was just a sweet, gloppy pile of noodles with a few bean sprouts and carrots sprinkled on. Lacked the complexity of flavors and textures that is what separates good pad thai from bad.  Pad see ew  was sort of bland as well.

It’s my first time here and they need to fix their menu online and in person..online it says the lunch special is 6.95 and it’s a dollar more in store and when I wanted to order the lunch special she said right now it only comes with a appetizer and on the menu it says a soup too I’m just really disappointed with that I hope the food is good
I am in love with this place! The food is delicious and the portions are huge!
Restaurant delivered late. When I called to request status they hung up on me.
Delicious
Good food

Ordered a simple fried rice dish, restaurant was practically empty.  Had other customers arrive later and they still received their food before me.  Waited close to 25 minutes with no one coming back to refill my water.  The fried rice was good, pretty standard and will hit the spot if you’re craving Thai but nothing special
Great food and cozy environment.  The chicken pad thai is incredible.
Really nice lunch menu =)
Delicious food, prompt service, great price!

So this is an update to my original review,I just had to give more info. I just gotta say my family and I love this place. I have always just ordered pad thai noodles,love them but just recently I started to be more adventurous and started ordering other meals. The last one I ordered was th cashew chicken... it is Amazing!!. Great taste,perfect seasoning. The appetizers are also great, crab rangoon, the spring rolls are perfect,  the ademame are also good.. I have to say this is a must try location. Only thing I don't like its the music, they play some hip hop music that doesn't fit the atmosphere..but hey,the food is what's important .. I have never had any issues, the staff is extremely nice,very helpful and very attentive to our needs. They go by our table often and take away what we dont need asap.
Didnt really care for the place
Great lunch special for $7.99. great food generous portions. No frills, but fun. The best little cup of soup comes with your entree, too. My go-to neighborhood place for Thai.
Great amazing fresh food for a great price too 👍
Love this place! Great food. Good for take away or dining in.
Good lunch special
Love their pad thai and green curry

Great Noodles, Curry, and Eggrolls! The ambiance is cozy with unique art on the wall and Asian tunes in the background.  Pad Kee Mao was excellent. The level of  spice in the sauce was just right for a midwesterner, but hailing from Texas I would ask for extra spicy next time. The onions, jalapenos, tomatoes, basil, and chicken were cooked to perfection. Great sized portion.  Red Curry was delicious. The curry was filled with basil, bell peppers, and bamboo chutes. The curry's flavor was spot on. The spice level definitely earned its pepper designation on the menu, it was spicy. I did wipe my nose a few times while eating. Great size bowl and good for sharing.  Top 3 Egg Roll in my life. This egg roll was extra crispy and filled with tasty chicken and veggies. The egg roll's shell was the perfect size, smooth, and symmetrical. I wanna attribute the extra crispiness to the fact that they might wrap these bad boys twice and I think they don't use traditional wrappings that leave the bubbles. They seriously are so good.  If you don't have time for a great meal at least jump in and grab an egg roll.  I can't wait to go back!
The food is great here and reasonably priced. They do a great crab Rangoon. Love the curry as well.
I really like this place because it's delicious and low key. Good for take out or dine in.
Best beef fried rice I've ever had

Quality and affordable Thai food in Wicker Park / Bucktown, a hood where ethnic food should be more greatly appreciated than the ubiquitous and bloated small plate, gastro pub, and different angle pizza joints. I recommend its takeout and classic Thai dishes as well as the house soma* on a weekday or Sunday.

Ordered from here for the first time using GrubHub. We got massaman curry with tofu and yellow curry with chicken. The massaman curry was good, but the chicken in the yellow curry smelled strongly of rotten eggs. We tasted it and it seemed like it could've been ok, but weren't sure if it was safe to eat.

Not sure why this has so many stars. The waitress was very grumpy today, which fine, maybe she hates kids, maybe she broke up with her partner this morning, I can give people the benefit of the doubt.  But the food, I can not. Too saucy, too salty, the crab Rangoon had some weird flakes on it. Excellent value lunch special if you can actually eat it without feeling like you're eating pad Thai sauce out of the jar.
Big portions, good prices, attentive service, and food that tastes authentic what is not to like
Good, cheap food. Fast service. Smells a bit musty inside, but great for takeout.
Really good food. Tables could be a bit cleaner.
Great lunch special deals and delicious noodles. Love the thai tea as well.
First thai food experience and it was delicious! Can't wait to try again. I would come back here if I come back to the area
I love the food. But u need to update your lunch special. I got here 3:40 and the server tell me lunch special is over. The website said 11:00 to 4:00.
(Translated by Google) Excellent seasoning!  (Original) Excelente sazón!
Good service, great food.
Good food. Good prices. Good service. Just go it's great
Delivery took over an hour and a half but the food was very good. Portions were average.
They have a great lunch special, which includes soup, spring rolls and an entree for cheap.  The food is fresh and yummy.
Unbelievable food staff makes you feel uncomfortable because they are so miserable.
Perhaps the best Thai restaurant in Chicago, which is saying a lot.
Stopped in for a quick dinner while in town. The food was fantastic! Will definitely return.
Good Thai option.  Tom Yum soup has been amazing and mediocre.  I’d like better consistency

In my opinion there is only 1 better Thai Restaurants in Chicago. Oddly we have never seen this restaurant but their delivery service is exelent. If you like curry order the Masson curry. I get it substituting peanuts with cashews.
Love love the Pad Thai and the service!!
Love this small Thai place, been coming for years. Would totally recommend the lunch special: Pad Thai and the Thai Iced Coffee!
Very good Thai food! Good prices! Great lunch specials options for $7.95!
The lunch special is delicious and a great deal too.
Love the thai iced coffee. Service and food is always top notch.
Thai food in Chicago
One of the best value lunch specials around.
Their panang curry is really good

Ordered for pick up off the lunch special. Beware!!! What they have on the ad menu does NOT match what they give you. Soup is not an option upcharge for brown rice that wasn't disclosed and when picking an  appetiser it doesn't give you a limit or choice to pick from. 2 lunch specials at $6.95 rang up to $24.00!  They charged for one of the appetisers. Again not disclosed on the phone.They did not honor what the menu. Sneaky!!

I order from here all the time. The food is excellent and delivery is fast. My last order included several special requests and changes to dishes. The food was still delivered quickly and it was great. It was no trouble to get everything exactly the way I wanted it. One of my all time favorite deserts is the banana in sticky rice that a lot of Thai places make. I usually get several orders worth to eat not only for desert but also for breakfast the next day. When ordering from here they always have plenty of them available (I've ordered from or visited several other Thai restaurants lately that have been out of these deserts) and they are absolutely perfect and completely delicious.
Beautiful
Nice food. Alright staff. Wonderful atmosphere. TURN OFF: NO ALCOHOL! but you can BYOB
Egg Rolls and Gyoza were AMAZING. The Chicken Pad See Ew was very good. My only criticism is the Panang Noodles tasted watered down.
Good food, good service, cozy place. Good place to eat.

I've been here a few times and the food is good and ambiance is creative.  The reason for the 1 less star is that every time I've come,  the customer service was sub par. A smile, interest in customer,   or suggestions would make the experience a little better.  Other than that,  it's a great restaurant as a whole.
Amazing lunch deals! Great food. I rwcommend crispy kee mao noodle.
Great value, solid pad see euw
Wait was long...we were one of two customers.  Soup they served us was warm and not hot
I would have preferred being in a lagoon
This is a cute little place and the food is always delicious. I loved everything I've ordered here.
I've been here twice now, and I have to say, the Crab Rangoon is my favorite of anywhere I've been! I'll be back.
Great food great service and nice subdued atmosphere.
Love this place. Food is always great. The lunch special is awesome. 6.95 from 11-3 soup crab Rangoon and an entree. Always take home some for later. Pro tip, don't sit in front window. It gets hot!
Delicious!!!! Great prizes. :)
Really good food and excellent service! I thought the veggies could have been cooked a bit more, but still really good overall.
The Crispy Rice Namsod Salad is HEAVEN ON EARTH.

Great fresh Thai food in a casual Asian like setting. Staff was great and efficient. Quiet place for a quiet dinner. Kid friendly. No parking in the immediate area, Oakley bus stop on Route 72 is convenient.
Nice restaurant. Affordable and tasty cuisine. I've been here twice. Appetizer platter. Crab rangoon a la carte.
Ingredients are fresh, food is always ready quickly, and their lunch special is the best!! Definitely a vegetarian staple for anyone who lives in the neighborhood.
So yummy!!!!
I love it. Good food.
Get the Mussaman curry because it is good to have.

Lunch special is great - $7 average for soup, appetizer (1) and entree... The soup is simple but good in a cold day (I'm not a big fan the strong green onion/cilantro taste). The appetizer was a crab Rangoon and it was good, crunchy and not super greasy... As entree I chose the green curry, it was delicious but too sweet in my opinion, I had to add salt to the meat... It comes with white rice and it was really good... I wanna come back during lunch and try different dishes...

I went to Thai Lagoon after finding out that another restaurant nearby was full house.  The server was a Thai lady it seems. I ordered the tom yum soup and the pad thai. Having live in the country with abundant of authentic Thai food, this place is pale in comparison.  The tom yum soup was not spicy and sour enough compared to those you have in Thailand. The pad thai is a bit too sweet. I guess it has customized to locap taste bud. However, if you have craving for Thai food, this is a quick fix.
Great flavor for a great price.
Food is very good with good services and good prices

Fairly standard Thai food.  Definitely better than average.  Good sized menu with some good selections that veer away from just pad thai.  They do good pad thai as well though.  Overly large chunks of bell peppers can be found in too many dishes and seems more like cheap filler.
Nice, fun place. Good food.
Super tasty. I've only ever ordered out or delivery, but quick service and quality food.
Really fast delivery and we loved the pineapple fried rice.

I got the green tofu curry lunch special here (but I didn't get anything but my entree)... It was good, but their tofu is very chewy. I would steer clear of that. There's also a lady that works there who was very rude. I saw a customer asked for something and she walked away and literally huffed and puffed and mumbled something under her breath. She has a very "what do you want? Hurry up and get out of my face" attitude. If I find out what days She's off I'd consider going back...
Great food -incorrect hours
good

Pretty good food - I wouldn't say it was the best Thai food in Chicago, but it's decent - especially for delivery. The delivery was timely which is definitely a plus. I would recommend the Beef Salad - it's pretty delicious with a bit of spice. The pad thai and pad see eiw were ordered by my friends and they thought it was delicious. Although I can only vouch for it via delivery, I would say it is definitely worth the price.
Tom Kha soup is amazing

Thai Lagoon is tasty and consistently good. The menu is pretty standard to other Thai restaurants. We had several dishes delivered and it was relatively fast! I had the chicken and broccoli dish and would recommend it.

Delicious thai food so close by!! Order the kee mao noodles and ask to get them extra cripsy and you'll be hooked forever!! It's also BYOB so it can turn into a really fun experience if you're with friends!
Friendly atmosphere and a great low key date place. Service can be a little slow, but a great place for a bite to eat!

Sweet & Salty, that should be its name. The best Thai food around, about the same as mall food in Bangkok. It's our staple "What's for dinner?" "Takeout!?" scenario.  Seems to have gone through an ownership/management change and I can't say I miss the hipsters. Appears to have genuine Thai people serving and taking orders over the phone, so next time you're there say "Sawadeekaaah!"  Tom Kah soup with veggies (no meat, no soy) is very good, and so is the Tom Yum. I would avoid the spring rolls as they are not worth the money. Go for the Pad Sew noodles with veggies if you can, although once in a while some noodles stick together and don't get covered in sauce enough.  Order for pickup and take their delish food home. Eat it on your couch and watch reruns of Star Trek - perfect weeknight.

Personally, I think this is one of the best Thai places in the area, even given that there are a few.  The food quality is excellent and the atmosphere is simple.  The prices are low making it a great value!

Very Americanized Thai food.  The noodle dishes are yummy but sometimes hit or miss with the curries.  They deliver quick!  I don't suggest dinning in because often they have scented candles burning that mess with your sense of taste.
lunch special was great value with soup and salad. They know how to make noodles spicy and tasty though the texture of the noodles need some improvement.
Great food at great Value!
